{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SGrirxANwuNq6sTtSYU8Me","type":"tool_result","content":"1900\t\n1901\t- FR-9 economy/rewards engine: queries for the three reward-economy tables in\n1902\t  migration 011 (`reward_config`, `reward_pool`, `reward_pool_fundings`) and a\n1903\t  matching FR-4 overview-metric helper. Backs the upcoming `/economy/rewards`\n1904\t  page without changing the public backend.\n1905\t- New `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-rewards.ts`:\n1906\t  - `listRewardConfig({ sql })` — selects `key, value, updated_at::text` from\n1907\t    `reward_config` ordered by key. Each row is annotated server-side with a\n1908\t    human-readable `definition` and an `expectedType` (`integer | float |\n1909\t    ratio | lamports | unknown`) from the static\n1910\t    `PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_KEY_REGISTRY`. The registry mirrors the seed in\n1911\t    `backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql` and the admin allowlist in\n1912\t    `backend/src/routes/admin.ts` (`points_per_dollar`,\n1913\t    `dogpile_default_multiplier`, `reward_pool_fee_share`,\n1914\t    `points_crate_drop_rate`, `sol_crate_drop_rate`, `sol_crate_pool_pct`,\n1915\t    `sol_crate_min_value`, `points_crate_min`, `points_crate_max`,\n1916\t    `daily_challenge_count`, `weekly_challenge_count`). Unknown keys still\n1917\t    surface (with `definition: null`, `expectedType: \"unknown\"`) so an\n1918\t    operator immediately notices a key the registry does not cover —\n1919\t    matching the FR-9 read-only-with-clear-scope intent.\n1920\t  - `getRewardPool({ sql })` — selects `balance_lamports`, `lifetime_funded`,\n1921\t    `lifetime_paid`, and `updated_at` from the `id = 1` singleton.\n1922\t    `null` is returned when the singleton is missing (defensive — the\n1923\t    migration inserts it at startup, but the page doesn't have to handle a\n1924\t    throw if that ever drifts).\n1925\t  - `listRewardPoolFundings({ sql, limit })` — bounded ledger read from\n1926\t    `reward_pool_fundings` ordered by `created_at desc, id desc`. Default\n1927\t    limit `PEEK_REWARD_POOL_FUNDINGS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 50`, max\n1928\t    `PEEK_REWARD_POOL_FUNDINGS_MAX_LIMIT = 250` — same clamp shape used by\n1929\t    the growth queries. Returns `{ id, roundId, feeLamports, fundedLamports,\n1930\t    createdAt }`; `roundId` is the `reward_pool_fundings.round_id` source\n1931\t    round so `/economy/rewards` can drill into the round that fed the pool.\n1932\t  - `getRewardsOverview({ sql, now, recentFundingsWindowHours })` — emits\n1933\t    one `PeekMetric` per `PeekRewardsOverviewMetricId`:\n1934\t    `rewards.balance_lamports`, `rewards.lifetime_funded_lamports`,\n1935\t    `rewards.lifetime_paid_lamports`, `rewards.recent_fundings`. Lamport\n1936\t    metrics keep the raw u64 string in `value` (FR-4 monetary precision),\n1937\t    use thousands-separator formatting in `valueDisplay`, and link to\n1938\t    `/economy/rewards#pool` / `/economy/rewards#fundings` for drill-down.\n1939\t    The recent-fundings window defaults to\n1940\t    `PEEK_REWARDS_RECENT_FUNDINGS_WINDOW_HOURS = 24` (clamped 1..720h) so\n1941\t    tests can override the window without touching wall-clock. Pool +\n1942\t    recent-fundings queries fire in parallel via `Promise.all` to keep\n1943\t    overview latency low.\n1944\t- New view-model types in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n1945\t  - `PeekRewardConfigExpectedType` — the value-type union\n1946\t    (`integer | float | ratio | lamports | unknown`).\n1947\t  - `PeekRewardConfigRow` — `{ key, value, updatedAt, definition,\n1948\t    expectedType }`. `definition` is `string | null` so unknown keys keep a\n1949\t    distinct visual treatment without faking a definition.\n1950\t  - `PeekRewardPool` — `{ balanceLamports, lifetimeFunded, lifetimePaid,\n1951\t    updatedAt }`. All lamport fields are `string` to round-trip u64.\n1952\t  - `PeekRewardPoolFundingRow` — `{ id, roundId, feeLamports,\n1953\t    fundedLamports, createdAt }`. `roundId` (not `match_id`) because\n1954\t    `reward_pool_fundings.round_id` is the column the migration uses for\n1955\t    the funding source.\n1956\t  - `PeekRewardsOverviewMetricId` + exported\n1957\t    `PEEK_REWARDS_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS` constant + `PeekRewardsOverview` —\n1958\t    same shape as the games + growth overviews so the metric strip\n1959\t    primitive can render rewards metrics without a per-feature branch.\n1960\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm test\n1961\t  --run` ✅ (370/370, no regressions). Frontend `/economy/rewards` page +\n1962\t  query/page tests are the next two FR-9 checklist items.\n1963\t\n1964\t\n1965\t## Iteration 39 — 2026-04-25T13:56:43Z — OK\n1966\t- **Log**: iteration-039.log\n1967\t\n1968\t\n1969\t## Iteration 40 — 2026-04-25\n1970\t\n1971\t- FR-9 economy/rewards frontend: shipped `/economy/rewards` against the\n1972\t  iteration-39 query layer. No public backend changes; the page reuses the\n1973\t  rewards queries already exposed by `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-rewards.ts`.\n1974\t- New page `peek/app/economy/rewards/page.tsx`:\n1975\t  - Role-gated via `getPeekActorContext` + `isRouteAllowedForRole(\"/economy/rewards\", role)`,\n1976\t    matching the existing pattern in `/games`, `/games/[game]`, `/growth/referrals`,\n1977\t    `/growth/kol`. Inaccessible roles render the same `role=\"alert\"` access-denied\n1978\t    panel without leaking section titles.\n1979\t  - Each query (`getRewardsOverview`, `getRewardPool`, `listRewardConfig`,\n1980\t    `listRewardPoolFundings`) is wrapped in its own try/catch so a single failure\n1981\t    does not blank the whole page; per-section error messages flow into each\n1982\t    component's `error` prop.\n1983\t  - Four anchored sections with stable heading ids (`overview-heading`,\n1984\t    `pool-heading`, `config-heading`, `fundings-heading`) so the FR-4 metric\n1985\t    drilldowns (`/economy/rewards#pool`, `/economy/rewards#fundings`) p